1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:09,107
=Episode 5=

14
00:01:21,979 --> 00:01:25,500
We only got married not long ago.

15
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:28,500
I only just found out
he's your cousin too.

16
00:01:30,699 --> 00:01:31,980
I accept it.

17
00:01:34,460 --> 00:01:36,099
Maybe it's just coincidence.

18
00:01:36,339 --> 00:01:37,579
Or fate.

19
00:01:39,139 --> 00:01:41,140
You never used to believe in fate.

20
00:01:41,580 --> 00:01:43,939
But I believe saying that

21
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:46,060
makes you feel better.

22
00:01:49,699 --> 00:01:50,819
I understand.

23
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:00,939
Zichen,

24
00:02:00,940 --> 00:02:02,058
I'm sorry.

25
00:02:02,059 --> 00:02:03,420
I didn't know

26
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,179
the person you loved was...

27
00:02:05,180 --> 00:02:06,299
was...

28
00:02:07,380 --> 00:02:08,699
Xu Nange.

29
00:02:12,260 --> 00:02:13,300
Nange,

30
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:14,778
from now on,

31
00:02:14,779 --> 00:02:16,139
please take good care of my cousin.

32
00:02:18,339 --> 00:02:20,019
He only looks cold and arrogant,

33
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:22,580
but he's actually very caring.

34
00:02:24,740 --> 00:02:25,659
Beiyan,

35
00:02:26,779 --> 00:02:28,620
Nange is a good girl.

36
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,900
Don't let her down.

37
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,498
I'm going back
to say hello to the others.

38
00:02:34,499 --> 00:02:35,699
You two talk.

39
00:02:39,860 --> 00:02:41,460
(That's impossible.)

40
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:44,419
(From what I know about Xu Nange,)

41
00:02:44,939 --> 00:02:46,098
(there's no way she and Beiyan)

42
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:47,780
(could've had
some romantic chance encounter.)

43
00:02:48,779 --> 00:02:50,659
(Something's definitely off.)

44
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,300
You're seriously still eating?

45
00:03:07,059 --> 00:03:08,180
What else am I supposed to do?

46
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:09,899
Him liking me is his business.

47
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,338
What's that got to do with me?

48
00:03:11,339 --> 00:03:11,979
I'm hungry.

49
00:03:11,980 --> 00:03:13,259
I still need to eat.

50
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,658
I'm starving.

51
00:03:14,659 --> 00:03:15,538
Besides,

52
00:03:15,539 --> 00:03:17,460
skipping meals solves nothing.

53
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:20,099
It'll just ruin my experiments tomorrow.

54
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:27,658
You don't seriously still think

55
00:03:27,659 --> 00:03:29,780
I came after you and Huo Zichen, do you?

56
00:03:30,539 --> 00:03:31,500
Fine.

57
00:03:31,539 --> 00:03:32,539
I believe you.

58
00:03:33,499 --> 00:03:34,459
Good.

59
00:03:34,460 --> 00:03:36,620
I don't like people talking
behind my back.

60
00:03:36,980 --> 00:03:37,778
From now on,

61
00:03:37,779 --> 00:03:39,019
we live our own lives.

62
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:40,538
Once the three-month agreement ends,

63
00:03:40,539 --> 00:03:42,220
we part ways peacefully.

64
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:18,700
Zichen.

65
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:24,059
Beiyan.

66
00:04:26,060 --> 00:04:27,580
Are you cold?

67
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:30,700
It's much warmer than overseas.

68
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,539
Actually, I know

69
00:04:36,099 --> 00:04:37,560
you still haven't moved on.

70
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,398
You were only keeping up
appearances for the Huo family.

71
00:04:39,398 --> 00:04:40,900
- That's why you...
- Beiyan.

72
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:45,379
I originally thought that once
I made something of myself abroad

73
00:04:45,380 --> 00:04:46,538
and came back,

74
00:04:46,539 --> 00:04:48,299
I'd finally be able to catch up to you.

75
00:04:49,179 --> 00:04:50,340
But I never expected

76
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,780
I couldn't even beat you in love.

77
00:04:52,820 --> 00:04:53,979
I didn't even realize

78
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,539
you were my rival.

79
00:04:58,099 --> 00:04:58,579
Zichen,

80
00:04:58,580 --> 00:04:59,619
actually...

81
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:00,539
Beiyan,

82
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:03,900
let's not talk about this anymore.

83
00:05:08,940 --> 00:05:10,140
It's been four years.

84
00:05:11,100 --> 00:05:12,340
It's time to move on.

85
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:17,380
After tonight, it's all behind us.

86
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:19,020
Nange was right.

87
00:05:20,675 --> 00:05:21,875
Some things are just fate.

88
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:26,619
Zichen...

89
00:05:37,739 --> 00:05:39,259
Ma'am, your VIP card

90
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:41,139
will be ready within five minutes.

91
00:05:41,140 --> 00:05:42,939
Mr. Huo specifically instructed us

92
00:05:42,940 --> 00:05:43,699
to prioritize

93
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:45,059
your requests.

94
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:46,260
Thank you.

95
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:51,738
I'll stay here by myself.

96
00:05:51,739 --> 00:05:53,380
Go ahead and continue with your work.

97
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,380
Well, well.

98
00:06:15,419 --> 00:06:17,699
Isn't this my dear sister, Xu Nange?

99
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:19,059
You came to apply for work too?

100
00:06:19,659 --> 00:06:20,780
Just passing by.

101
00:06:21,060 --> 00:06:22,179
Oh please.

102
00:06:23,380 --> 00:06:25,858
Don't tell me you're here trying
to corner Mr. Huo too?

103
00:06:25,859 --> 00:06:27,259
Didn't expect the genius PhD

104
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:29,979
to still have some brains left.

105
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:31,298
Miss,

106
00:06:31,299 --> 00:06:33,260
without an appointment,
you'll need to leave.

107
00:06:33,859 --> 00:06:35,220
Then what's she doing here?

108
00:06:35,339 --> 00:06:36,459
A broke student

109
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:38,059
trying to fish for opportunities?

110
00:06:38,979 --> 00:06:40,298
I'm here for an interview.

111
00:06:40,299 --> 00:06:41,659
I want to see Mr. Huo.

112
00:06:42,460 --> 00:06:44,059
This is Mr. Huo's wife.

113
00:06:44,059 --> 00:06:46,320
If you refuse to leave,
I'll have security escort you out.

114
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,059
What?

115
00:06:47,299 --> 00:06:48,700
Mr. Huo's wife?

116
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:50,380
Impossible.

117
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,379
There's no way she's Mr. Huo's wife.

118
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:53,979
She's a liar.

119
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:56,020
Ma'am,

120
00:06:56,060 --> 00:06:57,979
your VIP card is ready.

121
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:00,460
Thank you.

122
00:07:01,150 --> 00:07:01,899
(VIP Access Pass)

123
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:03,218
Please use the executive elevator.

124
00:07:03,219 --> 00:07:05,619
I'll handle the trouble here for you.

125
00:07:09,739 --> 00:07:10,098
Wait.

126
00:07:10,099 --> 00:07:10,939
Security.

127
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:11,780
I...

128
00:07:12,299 --> 00:07:13,419
Xu Nange...

129
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:26,659
Why did you call me here?

130
00:07:28,580 --> 00:07:29,499
Some things

131
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,140
are safer to discuss here.

132
00:07:33,179 --> 00:07:34,299
Come, sit first.

133
00:07:42,659 --> 00:07:43,940
This

134
00:07:44,099 --> 00:07:45,340
can't keep going.

135
00:07:46,539 --> 00:07:48,419
I'm really worried about Zichen.

136
00:07:49,020 --> 00:07:50,379
I talked with him last night.

137
00:07:50,380 --> 00:07:51,819
I could clearly tell

138
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:54,380
he still hasn't moved on from you.

139
00:07:56,260 --> 00:07:57,659
Living so close to each other

140
00:07:57,820 --> 00:07:59,059
isn't helping.

141
00:07:59,339 --> 00:08:01,059
Seeing each other

142
00:08:01,060 --> 00:08:03,259
every day will only
keep reopening his wounds.

143
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:04,059
Besides,

144
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:05,738
there are too many eyes
in the Huo family.

145
00:08:05,739 --> 00:08:06,978
Our agreement

146
00:08:06,979 --> 00:08:08,859
could easily be exposed.

147
00:08:10,060 --> 00:08:10,978
So,

148
00:08:10,979 --> 00:08:13,059
the only solution is...

149
00:08:13,460 --> 00:08:15,460
we go on a honeymoon.

150
00:08:16,020 --> 00:08:17,580
You mean, running away?

151
00:08:18,539 --> 00:08:20,059
Will that actually work?

152
00:08:20,940 --> 00:08:23,080
Like you said,
things have already come to this.

153
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:25,160
The only thing we can do now
is let time cool things down

154
00:08:25,339 --> 00:08:27,538
and help Zichen slowly move on.

155
00:08:27,539 --> 00:08:29,299
Until he accepts reality,

156
00:08:30,419 --> 00:08:32,779
we also need to be careful

157
00:08:33,220 --> 00:08:34,859
about ending our agreement marriage.

158
00:08:35,539 --> 00:08:36,658
Fine.

159
00:08:36,659 --> 00:08:38,820
It's not like we have a better option.

160
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:40,178
Then,

161
00:08:40,179 --> 00:08:41,420
we leave tonight.

162
00:08:41,699 --> 00:08:42,859
Wait.

163
00:08:43,699 --> 00:08:44,578
If it's a honeymoon,

164
00:08:44,579 --> 00:08:46,418
I can't go too far.

165
00:08:46,419 --> 00:08:48,058
It's in the supplementary agreement.

166
00:08:48,059 --> 00:08:50,019
My research can't be delayed.

167
00:08:51,860 --> 00:08:53,139
We'll stay in Hai City.

168
00:08:53,459 --> 00:08:54,899
Stay in Hai City?

169
00:08:56,260 --> 00:08:57,178
Huo Beiyan,

170
00:08:57,179 --> 00:08:59,139
you do know who you are, right?

171
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:00,538
If we hide in Hai City,

172
00:09:00,539 --> 00:09:02,499
your father's going
to find us sooner or later.

173
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:13,899
That apartment you used to rent,

174
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:15,220
nobody knows about it, right?

175
00:09:16,980 --> 00:09:18,580
Not really.

176
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:20,259
But,

177
00:09:20,260 --> 00:09:21,660
can you even live there?

178
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:25,220
It's a little rundown,

179
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:26,778
but for Zichen,

180
00:09:26,779 --> 00:09:27,899
I can manage.

181
00:09:30,579 --> 00:09:31,418
Alright.

182
00:09:31,419 --> 00:09:33,460
I'll head back tonight
and get ready to move.

183
00:09:33,860 --> 00:09:36,060
My room really isn't that bad.

184
00:09:42,819 --> 00:09:44,060
Oh really?

185
00:09:47,779 --> 00:09:48,658
You really saw Xu Nange

186
00:09:48,659 --> 00:09:50,379
at the Huo Group?

187
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,658
I'm asking you.

188
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:54,300
I saw her with my own eyes.

189
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,099
I find it impossible to believe

190
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:59,538
that Xu Nange could become Mrs. Huo.

191
00:09:59,539 --> 00:10:00,660
Mom,

192
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:02,180
I'm not over this.

193
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,818
That Xu Nange!

194
00:10:03,819 --> 00:10:05,820
Acting all innocent is one thing,

195
00:10:05,860 --> 00:10:08,379
but she even humiliated me
in front of everyone at Huo Group.

196
00:10:08,659 --> 00:10:09,298
Mom,

197
00:10:09,299 --> 00:10:10,739
I feel awful.

198
00:10:11,299 --> 00:10:12,219
Something's suspicious

199
00:10:12,220 --> 00:10:13,458
about this.

200
00:10:13,459 --> 00:10:16,418
I will get to the bottom of it for you.
Don't be upset anymore.

201
00:10:16,419 --> 00:10:17,700
How are you going to do that?

202
00:10:23,260 --> 00:10:24,899
We start by going to where she lives

203
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:27,139
and questioning her properly.

204
00:10:35,699 --> 00:10:37,259
There's only one bed in my place.

205
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:38,859
You take the couch,
and I'll take the bed.

206
00:10:39,579 --> 00:10:42,259
This couch is practically collapsing.
Can anyone even sleep on that?

207
00:10:45,819 --> 00:10:47,139
The door's over there.

208
00:10:47,179 --> 00:10:49,259
If you don't want to sleep here,
you can leave.

209
00:10:50,459 --> 00:10:51,379
Fine. I'll sleep here.

210
00:10:54,539 --> 00:10:56,259
But we need ground rules.

211
00:10:57,699 --> 00:10:58,499
First,

212
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,938
no noise after 10 p.m.

213
00:10:59,939 --> 00:11:00,578
I need my sleep.

214
00:11:00,579 --> 00:11:01,019
Second,

215
00:11:01,020 --> 00:11:02,778
don't enter my space without permission.

216
00:11:02,779 --> 00:11:03,739
This is my space.

217
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,259
Third,

218
00:11:05,579 --> 00:11:06,499
we take turns cooking.

219
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,779
I can't stand takeout.

220
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:08,619
Deal.

221
00:11:08,699 --> 00:11:10,499
Then I have three rules too.

222
00:11:10,579 --> 00:11:11,540
First...

223
00:11:12,699 --> 00:11:13,580
Get out.

224
00:11:17,819 --> 00:11:18,698
First,

225
00:11:18,699 --> 00:11:21,859
from 8 a.m. to 4 p.m. is my thesis time.
You are not allowed to disturb me.

226
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:24,019
Second, the fan stays
on medium speed only.

227
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:26,180
High speed affects my concentration.

228
00:11:26,380 --> 00:11:27,619
You don't have air conditioning?

229
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:29,019
A fan?

230
00:11:29,740 --> 00:11:31,220
You can leave if you want.

231
00:11:31,579 --> 00:11:34,339
Third, you are not allowed to touch
any of my research materials,

232
00:11:34,340 --> 00:11:35,899
especially the stack on my desk.

233
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:43,099
Then make yourself at home, Mr. Huo.
I'm eating.

234
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:27,720
That's what you eat?

235
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,640
Do you have some kind
of self-destructive tendency?

236
00:12:31,779 --> 00:12:32,859
I think this

237
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:34,058
maintains vital functions

238
00:12:34,059 --> 00:12:34,979
and fills my stomach.

239
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,019
Seems perfectly fine to me.

240
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:37,099
If you want something else,

241
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,420
feel free to order takeout.

242
00:12:39,740 --> 00:12:40,779
Fine.

243
00:12:40,939 --> 00:12:42,259
I'll cook from now on.

244
00:12:43,059 --> 00:12:44,420
You can cook?

245
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,519
What's so surprising about that?

246
00:12:47,519 --> 00:12:49,680
Honestly, the real miracle
is that you've survived this long.

247
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:51,139
I...

248
00:13:26,299 --> 00:13:27,060
Come on.

249
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:27,859
Dinner's ready.

250
00:13:28,437 --> 00:13:30,196
How did you make so many dishes?

251
00:13:33,659 --> 00:13:35,779
This shredded potato is amazing.

252
00:13:36,699 --> 00:13:37,779
Really?

253
00:13:41,419 --> 00:13:43,099
The onion beef is even better.

254
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:44,540
How did you make it?

255
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,700
I used pearl onions.

256
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:50,460
First, you finely chop the butter

257
00:13:50,620 --> 00:13:52,460
and cook it until fully melted.

258
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:54,259
That way,

259
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:56,219
it doesn't overpower the flavor
of the Chinese dish,

260
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:58,300
while still preserving the richness
of the beef.

261
00:13:59,419 --> 00:14:01,340
This is seriously delicious.

262
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:02,979
Eat.

263
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:07,499
Without air conditioning, aren't you hot?

264
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,600
This is an old apartment complex.

265
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,500
A powerful AC unit
would drive up the electric bill.

266
00:14:15,419 --> 00:14:16,859
What if I reimburse the bill?

267
00:14:16,860 --> 00:14:17,859
Then sure.

268
00:14:41,350 --> 00:14:45,124
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

269
00:14:45,125 --> 00:14:48,445
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

270
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:51,824
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

271
00:14:51,825 --> 00:14:54,679
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

272
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:58,520
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

273
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:01,857
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

274
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:05,561
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

275
00:15:05,562 --> 00:15:07,919
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

276
00:15:07,920 --> 00:15:12,159
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

277
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,720
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

278
00:15:15,162 --> 00:15:21,560
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

279
00:15:22,362 --> 00:15:26,800
♪Let me hold you once again♪

280
00:15:27,050 --> 00:15:29,970
♪Resting against your chest♪

281
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:35,561
